caption: Horrendous service. Food is great, but I’m never dining here again.
Carry out dinner for 2 by Galit was superb! Delicious, interesting food, beautifully packaged for home dining. Thank you, Team Galit!

I have eaten Galit many times as take out in 2020 and it is far and away the best Middle Eastern I’ve found in Chicago. The dishes are so exquisitely prepared and they offer some interesting items that are more than the usual Mediterranean fare (never tried Kibbeh or seen it on a menu). I honestly can’t wait to visit the restaurant in person in 2021 when I can experience the full menu. The staff and management are also top notch, and gracious too! Highly recommended!
If you want Middle Eastern food go to an Arab own restaurant... Most of them exist in the southern suburb in Bridgeview. Don’t buy this hot garbage

Today, we catered from Galit and I got to say this was the best Turkish food I ever had.  I’m originally from Brooklyn and know what amazing Turkish food is and this place beats all of them!!! Wow!!!! I’m impressed! Support this local business as this is truly a gem in hiding! Thank you for the amazing food and service!!! Best, Isaak

The only problem with Galit is getting reservations. There is a reason it is a difficult get...the food is wonderful! The Middle Eastern food is just a notch above the others. The pita could be a whole meal...the various hummus styles are amazing. The chicken dish is a must...Parking in that area is difficult so taking public transportation would be advised. The staff is quite knowledgeable ...Reasonably priced as well.

Fantastic! If you're looking for thoughtful Mediterranean cuisine in Chicagoland, look no further. The food was brilliant, an artful balance of perfected classics--crispy falafel and silky hummus––and modern twists––kale delicata tabouli and zhoug pecan sweet potato. The pita is simply the best (and fluffiest) we've ever had and left us dreaming of the day that Galit starts offering extras. Do yourself a favor and treat yourself.

Had the NYE pre-set dinner for 2 and it was delish!! I always love my experience with Galit but this meal in particular was so well curated. We also got a surprise set of cinnamon rolls which was a real treat. Wish I could give more than 5 starts!
Simply fantastic. The best Mediterranean in the city. Get everything and anything.

What a joke! WAY overpriced, and the portion sizes are incredibly tiny! Buyer beware! The falafel was ok, but laughable that they charge $12 for only 3 falafel balls, and don't include pita with it! It shouldn't require reading the fine print of the menu to learn that pita is not included with the falafel meal. (In that way, they can charge you even more money for 3 measly falafels). Next time I'll just stick with Sultan's Market, where they don't attempt to pad the already-expensive bill.
Amazing service
Grabbed lunch here while we were taking a cocktails class a few doors down. Great, fresh felafel.
We got takeout since reservation. Food was very good. Love the hot home made pita.
I mean I have never actually been here but my name is Galit so five star baby

Food was good but nothing spectacular. Small portion sizes for the price but it is presented nicely, little pricey though. Big fan of their covid regulation though, with contact-free ordering and payment

From the service to the food, everything was fantastic. They support their employees benefits by adding 2% to the bill. We got the impression that everyone there works within a supportive team, and that the presentation and kind service are proof of that. We loved the carrots, the rice, and the fish. Check this place out, it will not disappoint.

A delicious meal! Not cheap and the portion sizes are definitely small so be aware of that coming in. The falafel was one of the best i’ve ever had and all of the veggies - especially the carrots were to die for. also the hummus and warm pita is a must!

The serving size for the food is very small, especially for the price. If you're going to make me pay $12 for 3 little falafels, you could at least throw in a pita to let me FEEL like i'm filling up. It only gets 3 stars because it's one of the few places that offers real vegetarian food in Chicago.

Honest, straightforward cooking. Superior ingredients, prepared with care and presented elegantly but not overly prettied. The pita bread is outstanding! It's a pleasure to observe the kitchen crew who seem relaxed but super focused at the same time.
Fine spot for middle eastern food. i like it here, excellent food & service. i think i might become a regular. reminds me of a cafe in chicago i liked to visit.
Iconic history of our past
Fantastic meal, picked up several types of hummus and mezze, the pitas were INCREDIBLE. Kudos to Chef Zach and the Galit team, meal made my week!

Amazing food! The entire staff made you feel like you were part of their family. The owner and chef personally greeted us and we had a wonderful conversation. Don’t think twice about this place, your taste buds will thank you.

The best pita and hummus you’ve ever had. They do an incredible job of turning ordinary into extraordinary - you’ll never make carrots like this yourself!  The falafel is either the best or second best I’ve ever had. The in-restaurant ambiance is great, with amazing cocktails as well. Their curbside take-out during COVID-19 is safe, easy, and convenient. Please consider eating there during this time!
Ordered take out yesterday, it was awesome! Love the falafel!
So accommodating for vegan options and amazing service! Can’t wait to come back.

When you enter Galit their open kitchen is the show stopper- it’s beautiful & welcoming. It gives a hanging in your relatives kitchen vibe. The service is equally welcoming and gives does a great job helping you navigate the menu. Not pictured but Best falafel I’ve ever had- sums up my general experience here. Yes, I’ve had good hummus but this was the best. Also not pictured the steak over coals & parsnips are the ultimate flavor bomb. I’m gluten free (plenty of options for GF peeps here) but the fried fish got rave reviews at our table. I’d recommend getting the salatin because they’re great with everything. We’ll definitely be back here again. Make a reservation & check them out for a unique & cozy experience.

One of the better experiences I've had in a while at a restaurant here in Chicago. Impeccable service, great atmosphere, and amazing food!  We tried the course meal and they were more than happy to make it vegetarian friendly for us.  Every dish was clearly explained and nicely presented, besides also being delicious. I'd highly recommend the shashuka. Topping it with fresh herbs... perfection!
Flavorful and unique dishes

I will start by saying the food was very good. In particular I recommend the Salatim, carrots, falafel, and stuffed cabbage. The atmosphere was excellent and service was good.  I do NOT recommend this place for groups, nor do i recommend the tasting menu. We did a group of 12, and while I was appreciative for all of their accommodations to allow us a large group, the restaurant requires you to participate in the tasting menu for this large of group (I believe it is true of any groups over 6). They gave use one dish of each PER 4 people. I did the math on this, and if you ordered all the tasting menu items al la carte it would come out to be roughly $30 per person versus the actual price of the tasting menu which was $65 (for 12 people that's an extra $420). It felt like a scam. Ultimately, I think I would go back, but I need some time to lick my wounds.

Delicious food! We were particularly wowed by the brisket hummus, the falafel, the lamb and the Elvis in Israel dessert with caramelized banana. My friend also tried an orange wine for the first time that he fell in love with. Service and atmosphere on point as well. Great all around!!
One of the best restaurants in Chicago. Any of the hummus with their hot pitas out of the oven is on the short list of best bites in Chicago

Love love love love love. Probably the best middle eastern restaurant in Chicago. The staff was so nice and attentive. I got a birthday card from them, signed by everyone, which I thought it was super sweet.

This is probably the most delicious Middle Eastern food you will ever have. Everything is so delicious and savory. It balances out completely. And there's not a bad thing on the menu. I'm a big fan of the chicken for an entree. Definitely will be going back.

We visited this hidden gem of Chicago on 12/22/2019. It's a nice short walk after enjoying the holiday season light show in Lincoln Park Zoo  :) also because it's quite popular and late dinner time was the only time we can book. Make a reservation early if you can! We went for The Other Menu for $65 per person, thinking it would be nice to have a taste of everything they had to offer. For sure, we had some of the BEST pita and hummus in life (BUBBE'S BRISKET) - seriously, I can just eat the pita and hummus for a whole meal! Also had really original vegetarian dishes (CARROTS and BEETS) and great FALAFELS. CHICKEN THIGHS are really yummy and satisfying! I'd say for everything we have been served, food wise, it's a solid five-star! ***** :P For cocktails, I got the HERE LASSI LASSI, meh, not a big fan of the unexpected Asian spice taste in an alcohol drink :/ The only reason for the four-star is that our waitress messed up our order and somehow thought we were going for the regular menu (I didn't understand how that could possibly happen since she wrote down our specific picks for the Mezze and Hummus). As a result, they served some dishes of a larger size and missed some other dishes, leaving me confused of how The Other Menu really worked :/ Also the service was kinda slow. They did make it right by giving us some discount upon checkout, which was thoughtful :) Overall I'd say a 4.5-star is fair and def will come back again if I'm in Chicago!

After trying Aba, Ema and other middle eastern restaurants I was about to give up and declare that Chicago has no good middle eastern food. And then I tried Galit. This is probably the best middle eastern flavors you can find in the city.  Great atmosphere and surprisingly good acoustic. The service can be pushy with some dishes (humus and falafel) but generally is okay. The food was amazing. We ordered the Flowering Fox, Salatim, Falafel, Potatoes, Halloumi, Chicken Thigh, Coconut Sorbet and If Elvis Went to Israel. The only down side was the falafel, which wasn't superior to a NafNaf one.  Highly recommend, will probably come again.
Great experience, great food and the most allergy friendly restaurant I've ever been to.

Absolutely amazing food! Being a vegetarian for four years this placed surpassed my expectations. Each dish had its very own twist on middle eastern food. Best middle eastern experience in chicago. You won’t regret it! Worth the wait.

An amazing experience, proof that any regional cuisine can be elevated to a fine dining experience with high quality ingredients, the right skill set, and a passionate desire to do so.  Everything we had (and we sampled a lot!) was eccellent - even the basmati rice pilaf was a mouthwatering explosion of tastes and textures.  We will be back.

Large open kitchen with large pita oven in back. Good food, good service. Dining tables are very low and are interestingly uncomfortable for very tall people. It was cool. The food was excellent, and the servers very nice. Hummuses memorable of Shaya in New Orleans. Felt a little rushed, but still had to wait for certain courses. Pita is whole wheat so it is fairly healthy even if you eat 5 or 6!!
Delicious!

By far the best Israeli restaurant I've ever eaten at in Chicago! I recently returned from a trip to Israel and will say that the food here was on par with what I ate over there. The masabacha hummus was incredible and even the freshly baked pita bread was delicious. I also recommend the pumpkin tershi, falafel, Balkan stuffed cabbage and the basmati pilaf. For dessert, I recommend the baklava. The service was excellent, and the wait staff were very nice and helpful. If you're a fan of Middle Eastern food, you gotta try this place!

(Translated by Google) Spectacular. Everything is very good and the setting is ideal. The price is a bit high but the originality of the food is worth it. I highly recommend the spirit-free We Like Buzz Words, the Masabacha Hummus, the Balkan Stuffed Cabbage and the dessert If Elvis went to Israel.  (Original) Espectacular. Todo es muy bueno y la ambientación es ideal. El precio es un poco elevado pero la originalidad de la comida lo vale. Recomiendo mucho el spirit-free We Like Buzz Words, el Masabacha Hummus, el Balkan Stuffed Cabbage y el postre If Elvis went to Israel.

Food was delicious and service was superb! It was really hard to get a reservation but it is so worth it. Our highlight was the Balkan stuffed cabbages and chicken thigh. Make the reservation ASAP when you get a chance!

I can see why this place is so popular! The food is sensational, and I highly recommend everyone check it out. The restaurant had a large open kitchen, and the restaurant feels high-end yet also relaxed. Everything was great, but I can't recommend the steak and hummus enough! My recommendation: be adventurous and be willing to try everything. The olive oil cake was so unique and although I didn't love it, I'm so glad I tried it because it had such a unique flavor!
Absolutely worth the wait- made my reservation 2 full months in advance. The hummus is unparalleled, and that is just the beginning. I wish I could've tried every item on the menu.

Gourmet middle eastern fare.  If you enjoy middle eastern food, then this a must try - elevated classics; falafel was sooo good. Hummus & pitas - soooo good. And so on :)  Servers were super nice.  Would be happy to come back.
Loved it!
Everything prepared fresh and hot. Pita is amazing! Loved the atmosphere and ambience.

Great food and questionable service, the portions are very small and overpriced. Did not appreciate an employee benefits tax that was put on the receipt. Maybe include that in your menu pricing. Spent 60$ and walked away still hungry.

Three stars because I didn't actually eat the food. For having a reservation I felt like we were getting the shaft- got seated at the counter in front of the kitchen and right by the front door. Since it was cold evening and the door kept opening, we were forced to keep our coats and scarves on the entire time. The kitchen in front of us was messy and looked quite unappetizing- the last thing I want to stare at while at dinner is plastic bins stacked up slopping around sauces and hummus. It took nearly 30 minutes just to get our cocktails, and then till about 40 minutes into the eve to be asked to order food. At that point we were cold, off-put by the kitchen, yet very hungry. Quite frankly nothing was that bad, about Galit, but it was all very disappointing. I was expecting homey Mediterranean/Middle Eastern food and instead had a decent cocktail and left cold/hungry.
Pretty much need to go here. Full stop.

When you have early dinner reservations and the place is empty, you would expect a place known for service to make sure your water glass is filled. My glass was never refilled. I needed that water for the over salted foods and the medicinal cocktail. $18.00 for one over cooked, tough piece of chicken thigh was disappointing. If you want your customers to pay for your employees' medical benefits, make sure your employees remember to fill water glasses and bring promised pitas to the table. It's not a hard ask when the place is not busy. The hummus was good and the pita was good, but not for that price. Would've ordered more but the service never came back, so ordered dinner #2 elsewhere.

Friends decided to go here because we were able to get a reservation.  5 of us dined here and for the most part I thought it was good.  The other 4 loved it but I'm not a huge fan of this kind of cuisine.  Middle Eastern/Mediterranean food with lots of hummus. We decided to do the 4 course meal which was fairly priced.  I actually loved the hummus, especially the one with the trumpet mushrooms.  Delicious. The salatine course was great.  Small little dishes with very flavorful foods. After this, I could not eat any more as the hummus really filled me up.  But I was happy to see all the dishes come out. We had the chicken thighs, Balkan stuffed cabbage, foie torchon, shakshukah and the cookie. Everything looked great and my friends loved it all. Would I go back?  On my own, no, but if my friends all wanted to go, I would!  But I would definitely not eat as much hummus as I did this time.  Drinks were very nice.  I love any place that actually carries Plymouth gin.  Great Martini.
Wonderful food and service was good despite the whole place filling up in the first 30 minutes of opening. Make a reservation for sure
Amazing menu. Excellent service. Definitely order the cabbage and lamb entree as well as the hummus! Very pricey but a great experience and worth it!
I could have just eaten the brisket hummus for dinner... and I don’t even like red meat.
Food tasted good, but the prices are too expensive for the portion. We got Bubba's Brisket Hummus, Saldit, duck breast, falafel, and Hallumi.

Excellent  overall experience.  The flavors of the food were vibrant,  and the selection of dishes while small,  was on point.  One of the best experiences in dining for me in the last couple of years

Great selection from different Middle Eastern countries amazing hummus options we tried the one with white truffles which very tasty. Lived the meze options especially Turkish ezme with walnuts labne and roasted carrots with feta cheese.
Amazingly unique menu, outstanding service.
They serve a great food. You can enjoy a variety of mid-east foods. Before this place, I have never tried mid-east food though, I believe these were really authentic. Just come and experience here.

If you have the means ($$) you should make time to go visit and dine at Galit. However, it comes at a cost. Without sounding cheap, we spent $240 between 3 people on a meal and we all walked away hungry. That seems quite unacceptable in 2020. Every dish we had was beyond exceptional, the chicken thigh actually blew me away. However to defend my position, the lamb chop ($32) came with one singular chop. We were basically fighting over it, and that makes no sense. Great food and questionable service leads to a run of the mill experience in a town where world class dining experiences are everywhere.

Came here at 9pm on a Thursday thinking the place wouldn’t be busy. I was wrong! This new Lincoln Park restaurant gets booked out far and for good reason. A diverse middle eastern menu has something for everyone. Hummus with brisket is a must have! Foie Gras with Apple and almonds. Chicken thighs with shiitake and pine nuts.
First impression excellent. Immediately seated at reservation time. Friendly staff. A bit noisy and very lively.  Bubby brisket hummus is divine. Everything is delicious.  Highly recommend
Best shakshuka and falafel I've ever had

Unreal. I heard the hype about this place and assumed it would be just alright,  Hell no, I was wrong, so much better. The roasted carrots, brisket hummus, and salatim were amazing. For our main course we had the steak and the lamb....out of control..stupid good. Eat it.
I’m always a bit apprehensive to go to a place for the second time when I loved the first time as much Galit. Our second time was even better than the first! Can’t wait to go back again.
Amazing food and service
Really enjoyed all my food and drink! My favorite was the pita that came with the shakshuka and the kale tabouli. Drinks were also great!
Such diverse menu. Delicious food and creative and tasty beverages.
Wow! Delicious food & cocktails. Do not miss out on this spot. It’s a beautiful venue with an open kitchen. The food is to die for & the staff is very friendly.
Everything was excellent, food & service. I wouldn't hesitate recommending Galit to all I know. I plan to dine there again the next I'm in town.

I made reservations far in advance for Galit and I was expecting it to be a 5 star experience and meal. The decor is great, the staff was friendly and accommodating, and our waitress was really nice and knowledgeable.  The food was great. But for the price, the portions were small. The chicken thigh was $18 for 1 thigh!  We got the Masabacha hummus, which was great! The pita was so fluffy and warm. We also got the Kubbeh Halab which was small but super delicious. The Falafel had great flavor and wasn't dry like most falafel. Lastly the steak was great, but again, small portion, especially if you are sharing with other people.  For dessert we got the sorbet (which was good but nothing different), the granada, and the philo dough cake. All were very fragrant and delicious.  I would go back but only for a special occasion.
Authentic middle eastern flavors (I should know). The food is absolutely poetry.
I read all the reviews and was excited to get a table at Galit. But food was so disappointing! All you can taste are spices and salt. Not a real healthy food!
Bubbe’s Brisket hummus was outstanding! Served with a hot and pillowly full sphere pita is simply worth returning for!
Absolutely wonderful! Great food, lovely environment and the staff was attentive!

Wow, we came here because we were able to get a last minute reservation. I had heard so many good things about Galit and had been waiting to find a good time to go for a few months. We did the tasting menu and it did not disappoint. The dishes were all small but we were quickly stuffed! The pita is perfectly fluffy, and goes perfectly with all of the dips and the hummus. We got the Jerusalem salad, the falafel, and the carrots as our sides. The falafel was some of the best I have ever had. The cabbage roll with lamb was also incredible. We loved everything we tried, and I think this was a great way to experience the menu for the first time. I definitely recommend for first timers!
Nice craft cocktails.  Delicious food.

What an awesome addition to Lincoln Park and Chicago. Bright and Earthy juxtaposition of flavors. Try the tasting menu your first time to get the widest array of dishes. Great service and atmosphere as well. Smart casual.

Walked in and sat at the bar with a friend. Great service, great wine and all around an amazing experience. If you can’t get a reservation worth it to swing by and see if you can sit at the communal table or the bar. Great new spot in Lincoln Park

Went yesterday as soon as they opened because I didn’t have a reservation and they sat us down on the ledge facing the kitchen. I had such a good experience at Galit! Their food and service were great.  Takeaways: - their cocktail are delicious - Salatin and hummus were tasty and love the options - chicken thigh could have been better - would go back and get the halab every time

Galit was amazing!!! There was not a dish that we didn't love. The cocktails were unique and flavorful. The brisket hummus was an incredible flavor combination, and the hummus was the most smooth and rich that I have ever had. The pita bread was like a pillow. The smoked trout was very tasty, as well as the steak. Every item was cooked perfectly and excellently prepared. The service was friendly and very good.
Small bites ...Israeli style food... Good taste.... Can end up to be expensive

4 stars only because the service can be better  This place is on. Check this place out before it becomes too popular. The hummus is right on point. Smooth, light and fluffy; if chickpeas are paint, my tongue is a willing canvas.  Pros: Awesome hummus, Middle-eastern/Israeli food always feels health Cons: pricey for simple food. I can imagine my Israeli friend complaining about it  Photos will be updated later ;)

I've read a lot of reviews of Galit so I couldn't wait to go. After eating there I'm feeling it's vastly overrated. The food was good, nothing special. For Israeli food I'd take Abba over Galit any day. I felt the portions were very small & pricey. I was very disappointed in the Shashukah. Well I got it out of my system. Time to return to Abba.

Phenomenal place, with great vibes and good environment. The dishes were extremely good. As for the Shaksuka, it was a bit different, since the eggs were poached separately and not together with the rest of the dish. Still, it was extremely good, with a huge assortment of vegetables. The salads were great as well, fresh and on the spot, albeit with extremely small plates. The pitas were freshly baked and the spirit free cocktail was beyond words.
Great food!

Interesting take on modern Israeli dishes with good flavors simple but nice presentation. If it's your first time ask your server for help ordering. A bit pricey for this type of food . The service is first rate. Hope you give Galit a try.

An excellent restaurant with unique food that I have thought largely missing since coming to Chicago. Not only is it excellent Middle Eastern food, but it exhibits creativity in slight modifications to age-old recipes that are exciting to try and show a desire to improvise on delicious classics. The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, the staff are friendly and eager, and this is a must-try for both those who know little of Middle Eastern food and those who know it all too well.

I wish I could give this place more stars. This is my new favorite restaurant in Chicago. Try the hummus, I know it’s crazy to rave about a hummus but you’ll understand once you’ve tried it. Every item we ordered was outstanding.

Some of the best and most authentic Lebanese food I have ever eaten. The atmosphere, staff, and service were all absolutely phenomenal. It’s not very often that a meal is the main topic of conversation the day after you eat it—and my friends and I can’t seem to get Galit out of our heads. I am anxiously awaiting my next trip to Chicago just so I can come back and eat at Galit. What a tremendous experience!

Great addition to the Lincoln Park neighborhood.  Atmosphere was just a small notch above casual and quite spacious.  We went on a Thursday night and it we were able to quickly be seated at the communal table (a concept I love but I feel we don’t have enough of in chicago!).   Lots of familiar middle eastern dishes but by no means boring.  Enjoy all dishes family style.  Price: food is appropriately priced for the quality and overall excitement of what you’re eating.  We had: Trumpet mushroom hummus Salatin Falafel Smoked Lake Trout Foie Torchon Beets
Amazing addition to Lincoln Park. The "Other"/tasting menu is great, and may almost be too much food. Can't recommend the brisket hummus enough.
Everything well done, really nice Iraqi and middle eastern food with an emphasis on homemade pickles, labneh and great sauces!

We did the chef's menu and loved every bite. Hard to choose what was best but the beets and Bubbes Hummus with the brisket were certainly standouts. Tried a cocktail (maybe it had "shrug" in the name) that was fine but not remarkable.
Wonderful flavors bursting in every dish.  Very attentive wait staff. Interesting cocktails.  Highly recommend.
Food was delicious! Def a must try in LP
The food did not taste good or fresh.
Great food with a unique flare
Waiting for 1 hour for food,and after that the food was salty,very baaddd
Waited for food more than 1 hour....they are working really slow.
Fantastic middle eastern, don't be afraid to order lots of hummus and falafel, they will be some of the best for you've had
Wow, fantastic!
Had such an amazing experience. The food ws amazing,  service was spectacular (Our servers name was mac). Loved everything ws on point and I can't wait to visit again.

CRAZY DELICIOUS, middle eastern myself and I was enthralled with the food. My group asked for extra bread just so we could wipe down the plates. Seriously give this place a shot, I can't wait to go again

Good sharing plates. definitely get the salatim— the labneh, ezme, and cipollini onions with tahini were delicious; also order the chicken thigh with whipped Bulgarian feta and harissa - delicious!! The shakshukah was another great dish if you’re in the mood for something really ethnic that’s rich with a nice amount of spice; finally the grilled artichokes are simple but elegant with the lemon aioli, perfect amount of sweet and tartness combined; ambience is relaxed, we enjoyed sitting at the kitchen counter and watching the food being prepared. A great date night spot in Lincoln Park. Can’t wait to come back.
Delicious, unique, flavorful dishes in a lovely space. Great service.
The mushroom hummus is incredible! The fried fish was just OK. The chicken thigh salty. Beware of getting talked into too many dishes. Good service.
One of the (if not THE) best hummus I’ve had in my life. That’s coming from someone from Detroit
Had the tasting menu. Humus and stuffed cabbage were great. Everything else just OK. Weird to split 2 chicken thighs for 3 people all ordering the tasting menu. Drinks were not good.

I thought the food was all very good! I wouldn’t go as far as great, but definitely a solid meal. The brisket hummus and carrots were hands down the best we got. Not much you can go wrong with on the menu. The reason it’s only a 3 star review would be service. We were in the Resturant 2+ hours!! food took forever to come out in between each item, didn’t clear the other plates after we finished right away either...which is irritating. I would say they need to add more staff to get more stars.
Very interesting take on Israeli food. Everything is absolutely delicious! Get the Bubbe's brisket hummus. Very good attention service. Certainly recommend doing their tasting menu.
Excellent food. Comfortable atmosphere. Server was attentive. Even though it’s very popular right now the noise level is tolerable. Prices are a little too high for the food.

The food was really very tasty. There was a lot we really liked about the place but some things that we thought could have improved. Below are some of the "hits" (things we liked) and "nits" (things that could have improved).  HITS: -Brisket Hummus was amazing, definitely recommend -Ambiance was awesome, colors (especially the blues used throughout) and decor are very nice. -Drinks were really tasty and inventive -Chicken thigh dish was awesome -Pretty much all the food was tasty  NITS: -Expensive considering the small portions and we left with room in our bellies -Part of this might have been because they asked us to order all our food at once in the beginning. At a place with shared plates, we thought this was a bit irksome. -We felt a bit rushed. The moment we asked for the check they brought it. For a nice expensive dinner, someone in our partly pointed out you expect to be there for 2+ hours. We left about 1:20 - 1:30 after we sat down. -There was so many staff around, it was kind of intimidating. It felt like there was 1 staff to every customer. -Shakshuka was very heavy on the dill
loved shaya in NOLA so had to check this one out. Doesn't disappoint in the slightest. So many different flavors, and they're all good. not to mention the best pita in the world
A little too salty for me but otherwise tasty Israeli food. Fairly expensive if you are a big eater. Glad to have them in the neighborhood though.
Great cocktails!! Food and service top notch!!!
Trendy and great food but small portions and overpriced. While food like the fresh naan is amazing, it was hard to get full.
Food, cocktails and service were all FANTASTIC! Can’t wait to come back soon.
Very tasty.   Hip restaurant.  Vegetarian options.  Please go there, you will enjoy.
Delicious veg forward foods. Service and atmosphere we're great.
Every bite was delicious. Best falafel I’ve ever had. Pita, dips, stuffed cabbage and chicken thighs were all amazing. Staff was lovely and took great care of us. Would eat here every day if I could.
Wow! The food was an amazing blend of tastes and textures.  We had two lovely cocktails that were fun to see and drink.  I'm not sure but, the Kembo at the end might have been the best part.

Every bite was a delight. Each dish had flavors and combinations of ingredients that surprised us  Grilled breads are wonderful, the hummus is silky and buttery, the brisket spiced with cinnamon was moist and delicious.  And that was just one of the four dishes we shared  The place was hopping in a good way  We sat at the kitchen table and marveled at the energy and organization of the chefs at their stations, grilling, plating, and preparing each dish.  Service was friendly and attentive, but we never felt rushed.  There was no sign of opening glitches even though Galit had only been open a month  If you look at the menu and don't recognize everything on it or don't see traditional staples, go anyway. You will leave full and glad you tried it.

Just grabbed some small plates and a drink at the bar but had a great time. It was 9:30pm on a Tuesday and the place was bustling. I saw on Infatuation that the brisket hummus is delicious and turns out that's definitely true. The friend with me used to be a chef in Israel (which she kept broadcasting to our very amiable and attentive bartender, Hannah) and she liked everything, even wants to bring her Israeli husband soon. All the breads were crazy good. Surprising to see a more grown up, button up vibe being so close to DePaul. I kind of got the stare down at my super casual outfit by a manager when I walked in lol
Food was fantastic. Hard to single out a best dish, the fresh pita w/hummus is a must. Chicken thigh and falafel were top notch.
Try everything.

What a fantastic experience. The food, ambiance, decor, and service were all amazing. Everything I ate was next level. They really got the details right here. It's inviting yet has a sophisticated feel. You can get dressed up and go for a date or business dinner, or come in on a weeknight in jeans and t-shirt and equally feel at home. I was impressed with the level of hospitality and how at home I felt here. I plan on coming back very soon.
get the israeli cab sauv!!!!! so good. generous portions. a bit expensive.
The food was amazing

Stopped in on night 3 and had already made a few other reservations for other nights with other people. Let's just say I'll be keeping those. Dinner was delicious- that pita is otherworldly. Can't wait to try the few things I didn't order!

We hosted a client dinner at Galit and they exceeded every expectation. The wine pairings were excellent, the staff were attentive and gracious, and the food was no less than amazing. The hummus and pita is top notch, of course, but other group favorites were the labneh, falafel, and the Balkan stuffed cabbage with hand rolled couscous. We’ll definitely make this a regular stop in Chicago!
Really good family style shared dishes... original and tasty!
Really awesome!! The pita is heaven, warm and fluffy, and everything else we tried was stellar as well :)

Galit, chef Zach Engel's first foray in Chicago is an absolute must try. The city had high expectations for Galit's opening, chef Engel and business partner Andres Clavero exceeded the hype. patrons beware, very easy to fill up on salatim and humus alone. Save room for the the rest of the menu's delights. Small shareables allow diners the ability to try it all. The boutique eclectic offerings leave you eager for their next next seasonal dishes. Known for their wine pairings, the cocktails and non-alcoholic beverages are their lesser known delights. Excellent service. Great ambiance. Excited to see how these two shake up the Chicago food scene.

Chicago's most anticipated restaurant opening of spring 2019 does not disappoint! Let by a former chef at Shaya (Food & Wine best new restaurant several years ago) and One Off Hospitality alum, this Lincoln Park sort features small plates predominantly from the eastern Mediterranean (Israel, Lebanon) and nearby countries. Great addition to Lincoln Park! Can't wait to return.

Galit is EASILY my new favorite restaurant in Chicago. The atmosphere is so welcoming, the staff was friendly and conversational, and don't even get me started on the food. It was absolutely incredible. Every detail is SO well thought out and I cannot wait to come back time and time again. I cannot recommend this restaurant enough.

From the moment we entered - it was just a warm and welcoming atmosphere. It was clear that everyone working there wanted to be there and cared about our experience. And the food... AMAZING. Our table couldn't stop talking about how delicious and creative (and beautiful) each plate was. (Plus, amazing wine list!) Clearly crafted with care. Don't walk, run here. (I don't even live in Chicago and can't wait to be back in town just for Galit.)
Food, wine, hell even the coffee are top notch.  Doesn't hurt that the room is gorgeous and the vibe fun and casual.
Great addition to Chicago culinary scene.
